# https://clang.llvm.org/extra/clang-tidy/
#
# Disabled check families:
#   -abseil-*, -fuchsia-*, -llvm-*, -llvmlibc-*, -altera-*, -boost-*
#     Libraries not used in this codebase.
#
# Disabled individual checks:
#   -portability-avoid-pragma-once
#     #pragma once is the project standard for header guards.
#   -readability-convert-member-functions-to-static
#     Flags methods that could be static but are kept as members by design.
#   -modernize-use-integer-sign-comparison
#     C++26 feature not yet widely available.
#   -clang-diagnostic-builtin-macro-redefined
#     PY_SSIZE_T_CLEAN must be #defined before Python.h (CPython requirement);
#     the warning has no source location so inline NOLINT is impossible.
#   -google-runtime-int
#     CPython/libcurl APIs use long/long long in their signatures;
#     replacing with int64_t would break type-trait dispatch and API contracts.
#   -misc-header-include-cycle
#     Triggered by libcurl's internal header structure (external code, read-only).
#   -clang-analyzer-optin.cplusplus.UninitializedObject
#     False positive in external fmt library headers (read-only).
Checks: >-
  *,
  -abseil-*,
  -fuchsia-*,
  -llvm-*,
  -llvmlibc-*,
  -altera-*,
  -boost-*,
  -portability-avoid-pragma-once,
  -readability-convert-member-functions-to-static,
  -modernize-use-integer-sign-comparison,
  -clang-diagnostic-builtin-macro-redefined,
  -google-runtime-int,
  -misc-header-include-cycle,
  -clang-analyzer-optin.cplusplus.UninitializedObject,
  -readability-identifier-length,
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-constant-array-index,
  -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-do-while,
  -bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters
